===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|geology}} A spherical [[granule]] of which [[oolite]] is composed, formed by concentric accretion of thin layers of a mineral around a core. Calcium carbonate ([[limestone]]) is the most common mineral that forms '''ooliths''', but they may also form from other minerals such as [[dolomite]] and [[silica]].
# {{lb|en|rare}} [[oolite|Oolite]].

